@startuml seq-tree
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer — Sequence: git file-tree delivery + client-side filtering.
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this flow has two distinct triggers (initial
'' open vs. filter keystroke) that share a downstream render, and the filter path
'' never touches main — it is a pure app-db update that force-expands matching
'' folders. PlantUML `== phase ==` dividers separate the two triggers while
'' keeping one `file-tree` lifeline; Mermaid would need two disconnected diagrams.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Git file-tree — delivery (`vv:tree`) + filter (`:tree/filter`)

autonumber "0:"

actor User #white
participant "main.service" as Svc MAIN_COLOR
participant "git CLI" as Git FS_COLOR
participant "preload `window.vv`" as Vv IPC_COLOR
participant "re-frame\nevents/subs" as RF REFRAME_COLOR
participant "app.db\n(:ui :tree /\n :ui :tree-filter)" as Db APPDB_COLOR
participant "ui.tree\nfile-tree" as Tree RENDERER_COLOR

== delivery (on open) ==
Svc -> Git : `rev-parse --show-toplevel`\n+ `ls-files --cached --others --exclude-standard`\n(cwd = file's dir)
Git --> Svc : repo root + tracked & untracked-not-ignored paths
Svc -> Vv : `webContents.send`\n**vv:tree** {root, files}
Vv -> RF : `onTree` → dispatch `[:tree/received]`
RF -> Db : `assoc-in [:ui :tree] {:root :files}`
Db -> Tree : `:ui/tree` sub fires
Tree -> Tree : `build-tree` (flat paths → nested map)\n→ collapsible `<details>` hiccup
Tree --> User : sidebar shows the repo tree

== filter (per keystroke) ==
User -> Tree : type in "Filter files…"
Tree -> RF : dispatch `[:tree/filter q]`
RF -> Db : `assoc-in [:ui :tree-filter] q`
Db -> Tree : `:ui/tree-filter` sub fires
Tree -> Tree : keep files whose path\n`includes?` (lower-case q);\nmatching folders `:open true`
Tree --> User : narrowed, force-expanded tree

note over Svc, Git
  No repo / git unavailable ⟶ `repo-tree` returns nil ⟶
  no `vv:tree` sent ⟶ the sidebar simply does not appear
  (`file-tree` renders nothing when `:files` is empty).
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  | <#3A5BA0> | MAIN (git) |
  | <#9F8766> | git CLI |
  | <#B1951D> | IPC seam |
  | <#4F97D7> | re-frame |
  | <#7590DB> | app-db (tree + filter) |
  | <#2D9574> | Renderer / UI |
endlegend
@enduml
